text:
“the night” 
by: m 
oh take me back to the night we met 
you with your nicotine scented kiss 
i can still taste it 
the force you used while pushing me to my knees 
i still have a bruise 
the way you trapped me, forced me, abandoned me
but it’s the night’s fault 
it was dark
you couldn’t see the look on my face 
it was dark 
you couldn’t read my lips pleading for you to stop
it was dark 
you didn’t know my face was there when you struck it 
it was dark 
you couldn’t feel how hard you threw me 
it was so dark 
they didn’t believe me when i said i didn’t want it 
it couldn’t have been true 
he wouldn’t do that 
and when morning came, he said he couldn’t remember 
it was too dark 
#poetry #poetrycommunity #writersofinstagram #writing #writerscommunity #poems #poem #metoo #itsokaynottobeokay #yourenotalone

text:
i offer the unpopular opinion that men...have...feelings.
i consider myself a feminist but as a feminist, i believe that liberating women will also liberate men from the chains that society and socialization binds us with.

men can be fragile.
men can have feelings. 
men can be hurt.
men can be victims of domestic abuse or sexual violence. 
so not all men suck.
not all men are evil.

i share this idea because sometimes the fight of feminism can exclude men whereas i believe we should include men as allies because i am fighting to make the world better for not just my daughter, but also my son. 👩‍👧‍👦 equality will happen when we are able to step outside of ourselves and see lives from another person's point of view. #metoo #depression #relationships #insecure #poems #bodypositivity #women #womynhood  #influence #selfimage #image #wonder  #prose #sex #marriage #exploitation #metoo #words #thoughts #feminism #misogyny dreams  #rape #stereotypes #bodyimage #bodyimagerevolution #makeup #beautiful #pretty #womansmarch  #sexualassualt #domesticabuse

text:
yesterday my church finished another wonderful series called #fornepa . this series was one of my personal favorites so far. it truly highlighted what a church should be for, and our church is for helping people find their way back to god. my church does an incredible job doing just that. life isn’t always perfect and ideal , but god is present through out it all. this series has personally helped me heal in ways i never thought possible, and has spoken to so many people. if you do not currently have a church you can call home, don’t be afraid to reach out to me, i will be more than happy to bring you to my church. it is beyond life changing.
we all play a role in this world, we are all one piece to a very giant puzzle. it will all come together one day.
to everyone who has shared their kind words with me this week i thank you so much, they mean everything to me and are forever tattooed on my heart ❤️ our stories are meant to be told, not held in =] to my church, thank you so much for letting me share my testimony on video, that meant everything to me and i am so grateful!

we all play a role in this world, we are all one piece to a very giant puzzle. it will all come together one day.

text:
artwork & text by @dibujosfeministas
"• • •
no te pega pero: te cela, te controla, te humilla, te insulta... ✊se entiende por violencia de género cualquier acto violento o agresión, basados en una situación de desigualdad en el marco de un sistema de relaciones de dominación de los hombres sobre las mujeres que tenga o pueda tener como consecuencia un daño físico, sexual o psicológico, incluidas las amenazas de tales actos y la coacción o privación de la libertad.
el maltrato se puede manifestar de distintas formas algunas son: violencia de genero, violencia fisica, violencia psicologica, violencia sexual, violencia economica, violencia social, violencia familiar o domestica, en el trafico de mujeres y niñas, etc.
la violencia machista se puede manifestar de infinitas formas lo principal es detectarlo y saber que cualquier tipo de violencia se fundamenta en una relación de poder dónde alguien trata de dominar a la otra persona por la fuerza y contra su voluntad.
si sufrís violencia de género o conoces a alguien que le pasa, comunicate al 144 (#argentina)✊".
. .

text:
la belleza no es un número. da igual lo que te hayan dicho, porque nunca lo ha sido y nunca lo será.
•
la belleza no tiene medida.
•
no vas a poder encontrarla en el número que marca la báscula, ni en el número de horas que estés haciendo ejercicio, tampoco en la cantidad de calorías que ingieras...
•
solo podrás encontrarla en ti misma, en tu aceptación, en el amor que te des, en tu actitud... •
porque ya eres bella, solo tienes que creértelo.

.
.

.
.

text:
we all experience trauma throughout our lives (yes, including you). and though we may go through therapy, or simply stuff it down so it doesn’t affect us — the body 👁 and your brain 🧠 have not forgotten, they’ve adjusted. it’s time to live free again. 🙏🏽 .
.

i have seen a spike in harassment cases coming across my desk. businesses struggle to cope and even the city can't come to grips with this growing beast of an issue.
.
employees of the city of edmonton held a candlelight vigil saturday evening in efforts to hold city leadership accountable for the reported harassment and discrimination in the workplace.
.
this comes after a 2016 survey revealing 1 in 5 employees experienced systematic harassment and discrimination.
🚶🚶🚶👤🚶
"that's 2,600 people out of the 13,000 employees at the city that are experiencing this".
.
an overwhelming statistic indeed.🤔😓 and reports show it remains relatively unchanged.
.
while changes have been made to address harassment, discrimination, diversity and inclusion, it's execution has fallen flat. policies are only have the picture in aiding prevention.
.

.

text:
women + community //
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
something that has always broken my heart is how taboo the subject of miscarriage is. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
especially as i learned how common it is, i didn’t understand why we as women don’t talk about it more openly.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and i have found that this keeping to oneself happens with all things fertility, including difficulty conceiving and just feeling a lot of stress in general around conceiving.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the underlying thread seems to be shame.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
shame that our bodies don’t function the way they ‘should.’ shame that it is taking longer to get pregnant than it ‘should.’ shame that something you did may have lost the pregnancy.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and this goes deeper than just the world of pregnancy and fertility. women are taught body-shame from an early age. our bodies were given a laundry list of expectations before we could even realize it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
to look a certain way. to perform a certain way. to create life a certain way.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the power of the #metoo movement is more than just a campaign to expose and end sexual abuse against women. it is seeping into all aspects of womanhood and bringing us together, which is where we belong.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
women gathered together is an unshakable force. and we are meant to experience the tumultuous ups and downs of the journey to conception together. we are meant to hold each other up, to support, to love, to care for one another.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
so find your women, hold them close, and love them hard. we’re all in this together 💕👭

text:
marta sanz: el año que despertó al feminismo

a veces hay que detenerse para pensar con claridad. eso es lo que hizo marta sanz tras la huelga feminista del 8 de marzo. fruto del "desconcierto que provoca la saturación informativa" surgió monstruas y centauras (anagrama), un breve pero intenso ensayo que aspira a digerir la cascada de acontecimientos que han marcado la explosión feminista del último año: el #metoo, la sentencia de la manada, la carta de las intelectuales francesas... muchas opiniones, datos, revelaciones y sentimientos a flor de piel en muy poco tiempo. ¿cómo ordenar todo eso para no quedarse uno atascado en el enfado y la indignación?

para seguir leyendo ve a nuestra página teorías: https://www.facebook.com/baudiliomartir/

🔗

text:
a former university professor  in nigeria was caught on tape allegedly demanding sex from a female student is facing criminal #sexualharassment charges.

accounting professor #richardakindele has been charged with four counts of corruption, including demanding sexual benefits, sexual coercion of a student, misrepresentation of information and evidence tampering, according to court papers seen by cnn.

akindele appeared monday morning at the federal high court, osogbo, southwest nigeria and pleaded not guilty to the charges.

•	در ۵ اکتبر سال ۲۰۱۷ میلادی نشریه نیویورک تایمز این فرصت را برای برخی از زنان هنرپیشه که از سوی «هاروی واینستین»، تهیه کنندۀ پرنفوذ هالیوود مورد آزار و اذیت قرار گفته بودند فراهم کرد تا از رنجشان در این باره سخن بگویند. این کار اولین جرقۀ موج جدیدی بود که به سرعت جهان را فراگرفت. در جریان آن زنان لب به سخن گشوده و تجربه‌های تلخ خود از آزار جنسی مردان را بیان کردند. در ۱۳ اکتبر ساندرا مولر، خبرنگار فرانسوی با راه اندازی هشتگ balancetonporc در توییتر، آزار جنسی در محیط کار را محکوم کرد و دو روز پس از آن آلیسا میلانو بازیگر آمریکایی، کمپین «من هم همینطور» یا #metoo را راه اندازی کرد. با تولد این جنبش، شوکی سراسر جهان را در خود فرو برد. هزاران خاطرۀ تلخ از آزارهای جنسی در شبکه‌های اجتماعی منتشر و در پی آن، راهپیمایی‌هایی در کشورهای مختلف برگزار شد.

#کمپین #زنان #حقوق_زنان #آزادی #آمریکا #هالیوود #فیلم_سینمایی #جنبش #اعتراض #بازیگرهالیوود #metoo

text:
i don’t really know what’s been happening, i’ve only seen some posts. but my only opinion that i should share is that; wow... i mean. wow... consent is consent when a yes is shared between all individuals involved. period. -
i had something recently happen to me, it was a weird situation. i didn’t know what to do, i had to think quick. i was hanging out with this guy, i was actually happy because he was so kind to me. first time in awhile a guy wasn’t trying to just f*ck me. but, i was wrong. after eating dinner he cooked for us we were watching some tv and he tried to finger me. i said no. he told me yes. -
i checked my phone and told him i had to leave. he told me i can stay for another half hour. i told him no. he told me yes. -
i stood up. he grabbed my keys. i said i was expected home. he said ok. i left. i blocked him. and if i ever see him in person i’ll act as though nothing ever happened, but i won’t ever forget the uncomfortable sensation he left on me. and how pained i am since. -
-

text: one time i was told, “you don’t have a college degree, you’ll never get a better job than this.” i left promptly. never underestimate your employees or the desire for service to humanity. today, i appreciate her saying that to me, because it made me work harder and smarter. it made me get that college degree, which had never gotten me anywhere or moved me like my own soul for healing others. success is contained within you. stop dancing around it with those heels and start stomping out your love on the ground like it were the last thing you could do before you leave. stop questioning if it’s possible and jump into the vast pool. you’ll fail. i failed. i made business mistakes and life mistakes and body mistakes and child-rearing mistakes... and i moved on and forward. my clients all carry parts of my heart and soul. my children all carry parts of me that i am both proud of and question sometimes. all of us on this earth are so intertwined. and, yes, i totally sometimes look at it all, despite my very gentle nature, and say, “middle finger to my exes,” who said i was too feely, too geeky, too concerned with others, too lazy (due to being so feely), too all over the place, too grand, and the favorite of many “you are too much.” being “too much” is what i am. and what i am is fucking beautiful and now successful. chew on that. chew on all your words and misgivings about what i was capable of that whole time. and i want everyone to have this. because we all can. because your talent is no one else’s. because you’re going to do it different than i and different than the next goddess. we all have people to serve and we all have work to do as our worship. find yours. and fucking #doit. #femme #femmelove  #fiercewomen #fiercefemme #witchesofinstagram #womenempowerment #womeninbusiness #empoweringwomen #empowerment #ageisjustanumber #metoo #rise #riseup #hatersgonnahate #quotes #quotestoliveby #nastywoman

text: in light of recent events and certain comments made i feel as though this post is needed. us women need to stand together, the abuse and violence we face is unacceptable and closer to home than you may think. i personally face objectification, discrimination and obscene comments from men almost daily and i know the same can be said for a lot of my friends. it is not okay to degrade women and make us feel worthless, it puts our mental state and lives at risk and i stand behind every single woman that is subjected to this oppression. r.i.p to all the women who have been murdered/taken their lives as a result of abuse from men, you are so unbeliavably strong. and to all the women in my life, i love you and i refuse to give up this fight until it is fixed. #metoo #timesup

text:
update and trigger warning: i got some news this morning. the nypd is unable to identify the men who attacked me and will therefor cease to continue investigations into my case. what does this mean for me? it means that as my bruises and scratches heal, my mental state has suffered a set back. it means that i become like the majority of women who face the criticisms and backlash and barriers that come along with reporting but still won’t see any tangible justice or end result. if you follow my stories, you know what happened, but if you don’t, here it is:
two weeks ago (tomorrow), i was in nyc on a work trip. my boss dropped me off at my hotel after dinner where i couldn’t eat much bc of food allergies. after an hour of looking for delivery, i realized there was a place less than a mile away that had food i could eat so i went to pick it up on foot in times square. it was nighttime (doesn’t matter). i was alone (doesn’t matter). i had had two drinks starting several hours earlier (doesn’t matter). i was wearing jeans and a jacket (doesn’t matter). everything of value was in my backpack (doesn’t matter). i was diligently walking down the road, keeping an eye out for danger as women who are alone at night do. on my way back from getting my food, 3 men were following me and making crude, sexual comments to me. i turned around to tell them to leave me the f alone, as i always do when i’m being catcalled, but this time i got attacked. the 3 of them rushed me, shoved me into a wall, tried to remove my backpack, jacket, etc continuing with the sexual dialogue that i still can’t say out loud. i fought back...hard. y’all only saw my face in stories but my whole body did (and still does) show signs of struggle. between fighting and screaming, i was fortunately able to get away. but the damage they did to me, like many sexual assault victims far greater than what ppl can see. and now they get to get away too, except they get away w/no lasting impact other than the security they can do this again w/o consequences. #enoughisenough #headhighheartfoward #metoo

text:
jak powinna wyglądać skrzywdzona osoba, żebyś jej uwierzył?

może iść po diagnozę swojego zdrowia do lekarza zamiast otrzymywać ją od obcych typów z internetu pod swoimi postami? może nie czytać o sobie i wspierających ją osobach, że mają autyzm, są niedorozwinięte i głupie? może nie słuchać, że jest psychotyczna i bełkocze, więc nie można wierzyć w to, co mówi? że ma traumę, więc jest niespójna i nie myśli logicznie?

23,4% polaków i polek zmaga się z zaburzeniami psychicznymi. zaburzenia i choroby - psychiczne, neurologiczne, zakaźne, pasożytnicze, genetyczne i inne - to nie obelga. to rzeczywistość większości z nas - czasem przez chwilę, czasem przewlekle lub całe życie, czasem poważniej, czasem nieszkodliwie, czasem dotyczą nas, czasem naszych bliskich i znajomych. mamy się wstydzić, że chorujemy, mamy traumy, zaburzenia lub uzależnienia? mamy się wstydzić, że ktoś nas molestował lub zgwałcił?

sami się wstydźcie.

text: i was telling someone that i had bipolar. i was scared to death to tell him. it took me forever to get the courage to say it. often times when i tell people, i can see their judgement on their face. i finally got the courage to say it & to my total shock, he looked at me & said i have bipolar too. my first thought was comfort & my second thought was, he’s had to deal with a lot of pain. it helped to know someone who was traveling the same journey & fighting the same battle. so many people don’t understand but how can they, they don’t have to fight the battles of bipolar. don’t be ashamed to say “me too”. you never know the affect you can have on someone by sharing your trials. #theswingofthingswithbipolar #bipolar #anxiety #depression #ptsd #youarenotalone #metoo

name: Love is Blonde — The Play
pre_proc_tweet:
happy monday, everyone! while our  ‘taking marilyn’s untold truth to broadway’ is running in the  today we give you an insight on the playwright’s creative process. here’s an extract from  interview with  corriere della sera, la lettura, november 17th 2017 – just before our international opening in turin, italy:

today, in looking back at the genesis of the text,  says she is convinced that it was born out of “an ensemble of factors and coincidences, paly inexplicable, or explicable after the fact: a desire and an ambition to write about a controversial, revolutionary and tragic female character.” the choice did not immediately fall on marilyn, however. “for me, this was not an obsession,” argia stresses, “by which i mean that it was marilyn who chose me to write her story: a trip to new york in 2012 which then became a decision to finish my phd in playwrighting at columbia university, and to choose a creative project to produce on the spot. my first work in english.” the fifty years since marilyn’s death have brought with them the beginnings of a more complex way of talking about the star. “unpublished material emerged, never exposed. around that same time, my trusted bookseller literally put oates’s novel into my hands, telling me that to understand america, i would need to get through it.” _______________________

 is an italian playwright and poet based in new york. her previous work includes numerous plays that have been produced and published throughout europe to great acclaim, and has been featured at the festival of performing as in algiers, the greek festival of epidauro, and at the inda festival in sicily – among many others. argia holds a ba in playwriting and dramaturgy from d.a.m.s. (school of as), an mfa in drama from the teatro stabile in turin, and a phd in drama with a playwriting concentration from columbia university. she is a current member of the dramatist guild of america.

text:
in the wake of the #metoo movement as a response to the deluge of sexual assault allegations against industry titans, it is absolutely necessary that a book such as this which explores & interrogates the the many ways in which our culture enables rape culture  exists.
💫💫
not that bad: dispatches from rape culture, edited by roxane gay is a difficult, uncomfortable, but very necessary read. 💫💫
the anthology consists of 29 works by people who have experienced varied forms of sexual assault. the narratives are as diverse as the contributors. i won’t go into details re: the specifics as some of the stories - (understandably) may be triggering for some.
💫💫
whilst some of the essays are confessional, sharp, and punchy, others are reflective, conversational, and educative.
💫💫
there was one particular essay which stood out to me. i initially thought the piece felt a bit waspish and tone deaf. but, having confronted my cynicism, i realise the author is, in her own unique way, pointing out the many ways in which we have been conditioned to accept some of the seemingly innocuous manifestations of sexual harassment, whilst ignoring the long term impact on victims.
💫💫
there are many emotional, and lightbulb moments in this book. it is for these, and many other reasons that i believe ‘not that bad’ by #roxane gay is an important read - not least because it gives language to difficult situations that we otherwise are unable to articulate.
💫💫

• • •
in the 24th installment of the the best kind of worst, the #goodbrothers discuss our inability to get in some #5amclub due to our gym not opening (spoiler alert: chaos ensues when the regulars don't get their iron fix). we also discuss uncle boobah's recent triathlon training and uncle ole's recent spelunking outing, look over an interesting article regarding bohemian rhapsody, give our thoughts on some "sexist" comments made by country artist miranda lambert, shit on most of the recent superhero movies, give our thoughts on the california wildfires and the timing of trump's twitter comments on the disaster, delve into some odd (but effect) parenting tricks, consider buying some controversial christmas lights made to look like shotgun shells, look into the details of juul's decision to remove their "fruity" flavor pods from the stores, and give michael avenatti a grand ole f'yah.
• • •
p.s. the canasian calls in (on her birthday) and instantaneously regrets her decision. we also call tully and he instantaneously regrets moving back to the states.
• • •
sponsor of the week: arak razzouk lebanese spirit.
• • •

text:
💕the best strategy for dealing with limiting beliefs🧚🏽‍♀️
.
as humans, we all become conditioned to limiting beliefs. from the day we are born, we are told what is right and wrong...what is possible or impossible. but all of these things are simply one person's beliefs or expectations. we somehow, naturally take what we are told and it becomes our truth.
.
you can't make that a career.
.
that's too hard.
.
that's a bad idea.
.
the list goes on.
.
we can learn to lift these limiting beliefs that block us and hold us back from our full potential and living the life of our dreams.
.
first, ask yourself, "what is my limiting belief?" have you told yourself that you can't make a great living by being an artist? that your dream house will never be yours? maybe you believe vacations are too expensive?
.
then, ask yourself why. why do you believe this to be true? is it what your family believed growing up? did an old teacher say this to you?
.
anything is possible when you learn to detach from old beliefs and conditioning you have accepted as a rule in your life. realize, you make the rules!
.
you can have it all! all it takes is a shift in your belief system. so dig deep, identify the root of this false belief, and reframe your truth. who says you cant live your dreams?! if they can, so can you!!!
.
the only difference is some of us believe in ourselves while the others remain stuck in old belief systems. .
dig deep and make your dreams come true. i believe in you, do you believe in you?!
.
send me a dm or comment below if you would like more information about working with me one on one💓

"la féminisation du langage : utile ou futile ?" : c'était le thème de la conférence duelle donnée à la maison de la francité (bruxelles) et à laquelle a participé laurence rosier, auteure de "de l'insulte... aux femmes" (180° éditions), aux côtés d'anne dister, co-auteure de "féminiser ? vraiment pas sorcier !" (éditions de boeck-duculot). pour revoir la conférence, rdv dans la rubrique "comme à la maison" sur : www.francite.tv 🙈🙉🙊
.
.
.
regram @maisondelafrancite
.
.
.
bienvenue dans l'arène du langage ! nourrie par une foule d'exemples historiques et contemporains, la réflexion de laurence rosier nous amène dans l'univers des insultes, des insulteur.e.s et des insulté.e.s avec raymonde la syndicaliste, george l'écrivaine, nabilla la star de la téléréalité, christiane la ministre mais aussi colette, marguerite duras, audre lorde, margareth thatcher, laurette onkelinx, myriam leroy, christine angot, brigitte macron, les femen, les gameuses... la violence verbale sera passée au crible de l'analyse à travers le genre, les archétypes, les lieux, les règles explicites et implicites de l'injure en société et sur la toile ! 
en filigrane, on lira l'histoire de la "pisseuse": le sobriquet reçu avant la naissance pour déjà (dé)classer la future petite fille...
.
.
.

text:
here is an example of how alcohol dominates our lives. one of my coworkers had this happen to her at a large accounting firm, she didn't drink during her internship and was not given an offer as she wasn't considered social enough and they explicitly told her it was because of not drinking. 
in this case the man didn't even have to admit that the drinking was a problem like for myself and still ended up being discriminated against because he doesn't ingest poison. 
almost everyone i know in recovery lies about it at work except for me. they keep it hidden because they know they will be judged harshly for being honest for the rest of their employment.  my brother explained it to me, he would not tell his boss about his sobriety because his boss hated people who don't drink. additionally if he was ever late or anything happened he knew the boss would assume he relapsed because he is "just a drunk" 
i refuse to do this, to lie about the best thing that ever happened to me to satisfy the needs of other people to be comfortable. judge me, fire me, i simply don't care and will not lie about this because it is killing too many wonderful people 
this has to stop, we have to stop pushing this deadly drug at work and discriminating against those who don't want to drink.  we would never tolerate this with any other drug, why is it acceptable with alcohol?

#godry #drydiet #godry #healthyandwealthy #sober #weightlossjourney #transformation #empoweringwomen #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #mentalhealth #teetotaler #sober #nohangover #noalcohol

text:
sexual abuse affects the abused, this is an awful given. the fall out in families has a huge impact as trans or inter-generational trauma ripples out. 
in this weeks column, a mother wants to protect her six year old into adulthood. her own prevailing fear driven by seeing how her relatives life was destroyed by sexual abuse. 
the stories, the spoken & unspoken words, the tightening of your grip as you visit a relatives house where you feel uncomfortable relay the fears, the anxiety as you are hyper-vigilant to protect your child. 
when the circle of trust is broken in families teach your children to trust themselves. 
teach them to know if they are uncomfortable and how to get out and be safe.

teach them emotional & physical boundaries. 
teach them the language of consent - ‘no’ is a full sentence

teach them & give them permission that it’s ok to be rude, to scream & get away if they feel that something is wrong. 
even if they know the person or they are older. 
verbally arm your children about ‘good touches’ and ‘bad touches’. inter generational trauma such as sexual abuse leads to a loss of safety. 
teach your child to protect themselves & to stay safe. 
teach them, that you will listen, hear them and believe them. 
for the full article it’s in today’s @independent.ie

text: pre-recovery me had not learned/internalized any real and steady morals, by which i could hold myself accountable.  i thought i did, but honestly, i was stunted— self-propelled and self-seeking.  i would do literally anything to guard or retaliate against perceived threat.  i learned early on, the brutal principle of “any means necessary”. we learn what we live. right? 🤷🏽‍♀️my only consistent sources of guidance were fear, guilt, and shame, the gods of our family.  those sentiments could be counted on but not trusted, always present and never true.  today, i feel immense compassion for the terrified little girl i once was.  when we know better, we do better.  recovery offers me tools-a design for living, to replace the constant and lower companions of guilt, shame, and fear.  this has further and permanently separated me from those who rely on me to feel those ways.  it apparently, is not so difficult to manipulate a person steeped in those feelings.  i used to be fearful and distrusting of others and myself.  now, i am afraid of no-one.  i may not trust a person or organization, but i have faith that i can handle myself, by following the direction of my program.  i cannot be charmed, flattered, or bullied into doing things that go against recovery principles.  to some people, this is an act of hostility, willfulness, war…like “if you cannot control me, then i must be trying to control you”  but that is sick and foolish thinking.  i am only controlling only myself—neither a crime nor an attack—the exact opposite.  in recovery, we learn to “live and let live”. that is what i aim to do.  my life is built around being the best mother, friend, girlfriend, neighbor, employee that i can be.  these are my causes, not my roles.  i serve as faithfully as i can, one day at a time.  some days are better than others. my motives finally are tethered to service in something much greater than my own will.  in this way, i feel i am now living right, but not perfectly.  i am a work in progress. #morals #martinlutherking #wise #spiritual #leader #teacher #benevolence #ruthless

text:
interesting article about changes made to holiday parties as a fallout from the #metoo movement and owners being concerned about the potential for sexual assault when excessive drinking is taking place. 
it's great to see this happening but makes me a bit sad as there is no mention of the recovery community and how alcohol dominates so many interactions, even at work we are judged for remaining sober. "i'm creating a safer environment for everyone," says davia, owner of beeya, a job search website based in irvine, california. "while i know it can be seen as 'not fair' for banning alcohol from our holiday party, i would respond saying it's 'not fair' for anyone to feel uncomfortable especially in their place of work

for millions of people in recovery alcohol makes them uncomfortable and being forced to be around it is harmful to their recovery. is that fair? it's not even taken into consideration, that's how far away we are from understanding the addiction epidemic and alcohols dominance in our lives. there was no mention of the addiction epidemic and recovery community in this article. there never is, it's as if it's happening in a different country to different people.  news flash - it's happening right here, right now to the people we work with, our neighbors and family and friends. it's certainly wonderful to have some acknowledgement of the issue in any capacity but let's remember that alcohol is a highly addictive drug that kills so many wonderful people each year and we need to be more accepting of someone's decision to say no thanks and stop pushing it at work. so many people tell me their drinking became worse after college because of the free unlimited alcohol 
let's hope that movements like this continue and we begin to recognize the needs of the recovery community in the future. 
#godry #drydiet #godry #healthyandwealthy #sober #weightlossjourney #transformation #empoweringwomen #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #mentalhealth #teetotaler #sober #nohangover

text:
hiljaisuus ei ole aina myöntymisen merkki. se on toisinaan merkki pakokauhusta. lamaantumisesta siihen paikkaan.

olin 12 ja se oli 14. pyyntö, jota oikeasti ymmärtämättä. suostumus, oikeasti tajuamatta mihin. olin 24, ennen kuin pystyin puhua tästä kenellekkään. suun avaaminen hävetti niin perkeleesti. minua, joka aina sanoo, ettei häpeää tunne.

olin 18 ja kännissä. pitkään ajattelin sen olevan osasyy kaikkeen. mut eihän sammuneena ole edes tietoinen. ei tietoinen siitä, mihin toisen käsi on kulkeutunut tai ainakin minne se olisi halunnut.

paria viikkoa myöhemmin, olin edelleen 18. hämyiset jatkot. se sama tyyppi, jota joskus ystäväksi kutsuin. tykkäs musta liikaa. polttoaineena alkoholi, otti ranteista kiinni ja mentaliteetti oli, että jos ei hyvällä, niin sitten pahalla. 
joku voima, adrenaliini kai. sai mut pois tilanteesta

mutta miksi jäin nukkumaan sinne? muistan vieläkin sen pelon. pelon, että jos sulkee silmät, niin entä jos se taas?

meni vuosia ennen ku tajusin kutsua noita rikoksiksi, häirinnäksi, vallanväärinkäytöksi. kunhan eihän mikään mennyt loppuun asti, ajattelin.
menihän se riittävästi. se meni häpeään, itsesyyttelyyn ja luihin ja ytimiin niin, että sitä tunsi itsensä pilatuksi ja likaiseksi.

mutta en mä oo pilalla. mä oon selvinnyt ja selviän ja elän ja nautin ja nauran. muhun saa koskea, kunhan pidät musta huolta.

text:
_____________________________________________________________ ❓❓what would you do differently if you dropped the fear of anyone judging you❓❓ mine would be singing more, and then sharing more of my music. and i'm not talking about the "flawless" versions, the perfectionist inside of me dreams of. i want to be brave enough to share the raw and super emotional moments like this, where there are some mistakes -but even more passion and heart. 
on this day, i literally hid from all responsibility, in the apartment complex pool room, so that i could have an hour to myself for some #musictherapy.

text:
japanese journalist shiori ito is telling assembled participants at the world forum for democracy about her rape after being drugged by a veteran journalist with connections to high level politicians. for reporting the rape, ms ito was chastised by male politicians in japan, who dismissed her case as "error in judgment." as her ordeal gained publicity in japan, she received abuse and threats of violence and death online and offline; she even had to go into hiding. japan's backward, conservative attitude towards gender equality (age of consent being 13-years-old; and a rape penalty of 3 years, even tho burglary gets 5 years) saw her case disparaged and neglected by their national media. that is, until the #metoo movement happened around the world, followed by an article on her case in the ny times -- the international attention forcing japan to finally pay attention. ms ito emphasised that when the system fails to work at home, international attention and support can push those wheels of justice that refuse to move. her brave testimony here earned her a prolonged ovation; and rightly so. .
.
.
#worldforumfordemocracy #genderequality #councilofeurope #strasbourg

text:
a lot of people are prepping for holiday travel this week. here’s a #podcast you might enjoy while on the road: season 3 of the 30 for 30 series: #bikram.
.
bikram yoga has been huge for decades. yogis learned the moves and opened their own franchise studios. the man, though, proved to be a predator.
.
it’s an unfortunate entry in the #metoo era. people found themselves in the yoga, but lost an important part of themselves when he sexually assaulted them. it’s a fascinating series that gives a thorough and respectful look at what went wrong.
.

text:
if you haven’t shopped during previous small business saturdays, you’ve been missing out. and, if you’re a veteran of the holiday, get ready because this is going to be the best year yet! but don’t just take my word for it, let me explain why small business saturday® is so important and enumerate the many reasons why you’ll want to invest in your community on november 24th this year.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the bra boutique by the bra network is a pop-up shop that celebrates small business saturday® by creating a brick-and-mortar experience for women-owned businesses in los angeles. we’re shining a spotlight on some very talented entrepreneurs, and opening doors to gain more exposure for their brands. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
some of the participating businesses in this year’s event include lahive (fashion line designed and made in downtown los angeles), maile by design (ethically-produced jewelry, handmade in los angeles), and the manifest box (a gift box where you can find education, resources, and hand-picked tools and talismans, and endless inspiration for a beautiful, intentional life). courtney paige ray, branding photographer, will also be setting up a pop-up studio for branding portraits for entrepreneurs.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ come join us on saturday, november 24th, from 11 am - 4 pm at open mind art space (11631 santa monica blvd.).⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
. #savoircollabseries #savoircollab #savoirwoman #womenwhoknow #femalefounders #womenwholead #changemakers #womensupportingotherwomen #entrepreneur #metoo #equalityforall #womenempowerment #wedoevents #experientialmarketing #experientialevents #eventproducer #influencermarketing #art #experiential #popup #liveevent #irl #womenownedbusiness #smallbusinesssaturday #smallbusinessowner

text:
85 years since women were entitled to vote in spain.
.
the second republic (1931-1936) generated important legislative work and women were granted many new rights of which they had been deprived. the 1931 constitution granted suffrage to women. 
spain was therefore one of the first among south european states to enfranchise women. in 1932, laws on divorce and civil marriage were passed. women were accorded full legal status ; abortion was legalised, the crime of adultery was abolished and legal measures ensuring women's equal access to the labour market were taken. 📷 clara campoamor. .
.
.

text:
let’s co-create the future of masculinity. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
less than two weeks until the conscious masculinity intensive starts online. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
men, masculine people, parents of boys, this is for all of us. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
two weeks of daily lessons, action steps, live coaching, guided meditation, and community support. lifetime access so you can take your time with the content. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
we’re diving into all of this and more: our masculinity stories, healing the old, choosing the new; the intertwined roots of race & gender & sexuality; #metoo and bystander intervention; how to talk to other men about masculinity; feminism and men's role in the movement; relationships: emotional intelligence + emotional labor; workplace: gender equity + leading from a place of integrity; allyship + authenticity: building mutually supportive connections; social media: navigating callouts + creating community; + more! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
you in? sign up link in bio. there are 3 pricing tiers to make it as accessible as possible. you can also donate a ticket for folks in need. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
even if you’re not feeling aligned with doing this intensive at this time, if you’re a man and you have the resources, consider donating a ticket so that others can access this important work. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
thank you to everyone who’s been showing up and engaging in these conversations and doing this work. love you all <3 ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
p.s. image text from my recent piece on @the_numinous (linked in bio)⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
#consciousmasculinity #healthymasculinity #divinemasculine #masculinity #ftm

text:
stop pseudo feminism
its not just about ignoring the #metoo or any #hetoo
but the world is all about #wetwo
and if this has to prevail then lets take this quote in the right spirits.
i am no #misogynist and aint need to prove that. 
but 
lets not make way for useless stir
& sideline the actualities
under a sensational facade of #pseudo #feminism 
lets not create unnecessary conflict & hassles under a sensational hoax of #pseudofeminism
lets not create an environment of rebel against the opposite gender under a sensational cloak of #pseudofeminism
lets not become an enemy for your own gender under a dubious & sensational tag of #pseudo #feminism 
lets strongly condemn & reprimand the appalling & heinous deeds being actually done & stand against the real discrimination being taking place
but lets not get the trivialities & vested interests addressed under the branding of #feminism 
please stop being #pseudofeminist and garner the limelight & get ignorant towards the ones who seriously need our attention and support.
stand for the genuine rights of your gender but do not take undue advantage of it.
stop being a pseudo feminist.
#mywords #realitycheck #quotes #musings #nomisogyny #genderequality #women #men #equality 
#jaihind
#wordsnotspoken

text:
let’s co-create the future of masculinity. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
less than two weeks until the conscious masculinity intensive starts online. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
men, masculine people, parents of boys, this is for all of us. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
two weeks of daily lessons, action steps, live coaching, guided meditation, and community support. lifetime access so you can take your time with the content. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
we’re diving into all of this and more: our masculinity stories, healing the old, choosing the new; the intertwined roots of race & gender & sexuality; #metoo and bystander intervention; how to talk to other men about masculinity; feminism and men's role in the movement; relationships: emotional intelligence + emotional labor; workplace: gender equity + leading from a place of integrity; allyship + authenticity: building mutually supportive connections; social media: navigating callouts + creating community; + more! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
you in? sign up link in bio. there are 3 pricing tiers to make it as accessible as possible. you can also donate a ticket for folks in need. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
even if you’re not feeling aligned with doing this intensive at this time, if you’re a man and you have the resources, consider donating a ticket so that others can access this important work. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
thank you to everyone who’s been showing up and engaging in these conversations and doing this work. love you all <3 ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
p.s. image text from my recent piece on @the_numinous (linked in bio)⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
#consciousmasculinity #healthymasculinity #divinemasculine #masculinity #ftm

giving up because of fear is something you may not survive.

text: for women who work in federal prisons, where they are vastly outnumbered by male colleagues and male inmates, concealing every trace of their femininity is both necessary and, ultimately, futile. every day is a terrifying exercise in avoiding harassment not just from inmates, but male co-workers and bosses. a times investigation found that the women who report harassment face retaliation, professional sabotage and even termination — while the careers of many harassers and those who protect them flourish. today, women make up a third of the bureau of prisons’ work force, holding jobs from secretary to regional director, overseeing an inmate population that is 93 percent male. but there is a feeling that they have never fully been accepted or treated as equals — and many say that little to nothing has changed for those who dare to speak up since #metoo. 📸: @alyssaschukar

text:
l-r: repair co-founder claudia pena, event host saul sarabia, storytellers dean steckman, susan burton, gabriela sanchez meraz @_gabriela819, vocalist danette wilson @shsblsd, guitarist shaunie duncan @shaunie duncan 
so much gratitude! today's storytelling event, "clarity" was such a joy! we continue to be deeply affected by the courage, vulnerability, brilliance, generosity and strength of our storytellers and collaborators in the "transformation" storytelling series. it was powerful today to be in community with storytellers susan burton, jerrika hinton @hellojerrika, dean steckman and gabriela sanchez meraz, host/emcee saul sarabia, vocalist danette wilson, and guitarist shaunie duncan! 
we also want to thank daniel umana and ava at mercado la paloma @mercadolapaloma, our volunteers rachel yiv, kacie magoski @kaciemagoski and kristina david, harris rashid for additional tech support, our graphic designer marium mohiuddin @mpracca, and our co-sponsors, a new way of life re-entry project @anewwayoflifela and ralph j. bunche center for african american studies at ucla @bunchecenter

text:
packaged
a creative art workshop: comfort and discomfort boxes
december 11th | 7pm

led by adler university art therapy & counseling graduate students:
abbie brinker & deanna digiulio

here at awakenings, we provide a sanctuary for survivors of sexual assault and their art. packaged will be an arts workshop that will integrate the idea of self-exploration with creative art making and crafting. we invite those who have experienced sexual violence and their allies to come together in a safe environment, to think critically about what brings them comfort, and what brings them discomfort. led by adler university graduate art therapy & counseling students abbie brinker and deanna digiulio, packaged will give an outlet to survivors and their supporters to create a box or vessel that contains ideas, thoughts, or experiences that bring them some kind of joy or provide from discomfort. we encourage guests to bring their own box or vessel, but all other arts and craft materials including extra boxes will be provided to create these ideas and place them inside your box. guests will also be welcome to bring any items they feel would fit well within their box. for those who make comfort boxes, packaged will help turn hope and happiness into something tangible that can be kept and reexamined in times of discomfort. for those who make discomfort boxes, packaged turns discomforts into something tangible that can be thrown away or destroyed.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#chicagoart #chicagononprofit #chicagogallery #sexualassault #advocacy #survivorart #artsed #artwatchers #metoo #believesurvivors #metoomvmt #workshop #selfcare

text:
via abc action news: a utah police officer has gone viral on social media after photos were posted by the west jordan police department of him holding a young mother's baby as she filed a domestic violence report. 
officer lofgran is being praised for helping the mother. 
according to the facebook post, a young mother came in to the department with her small children to file a domestic violence report and officer lofgran helped watch over the children while the mother got the help she needed. 
the department says the officer spend hours on the call, helping the mother with her children so her report could be filed. 
the post has been shared nearly 500 times on facebook.

text:
🚩 *पत्रकारों व हिंदुनिष्ठों के लिए कानुन अलग-अलग है?* 19 नवम्बर 2018
www.azaadbharat.org 🚩आजकल जितनी तेजी से भारत में कानूनों के मायने बदल जाते हैं उतनी तेजी से तो शायद आप टेलिविज़न में चैनल भी नहीं बदल पाते होंगे । जी हाँ आजकल हमारे देश के कानूनों में बहुत ही शीघ्रता से परिवर्तन होता नजर आता है । 🚩और वो भी बात अगर किसी हिन्दू संत या हिन्दू धर्म के किसी प्रतिनिधि की हो तो फिर कहना ही क्या? 🚩वर्तमान की स्थिति देखकर लगता है कि कानून के नियम नेता-अभिनेता एवं अमीर और पत्रकारों के लिए अलग और किसी हिंदुनिष्ठ या हिन्दू साधु-संत के लिए अलग-अलग होते हैं ।  किसी हिन्दू धर्म के संत या हिंदुत्व का प्रतिनिधित्व करने वालों पर मात्र एक आरोप लगने की देर होती है और उनकी गिरफ्तारी हो जाती है तथा मीडिया की झूठी कहानियों की पट्टियां भी शुरू हो जाती है, लेकिन वहीं अगर कोई नेता-अभिनेता या पत्रकार अथवा किसी अन्य धर्म के धर्म गुरु हों तो उनके द्वारा किये गए दुष्कृत्यों पर मीडिया और पुलिस मूकदर्शक बन बैठ जाते हैं और न्यायलय से उन्हें जमानत भी तुरंत दे दी जाती है । 🚩ऐसे कई केस हमने देखे  तरुण तेजपाल, दीपक चौरसिया, सलमान खान, लालू यादव, विजय माल्या इन सबके आरोप सिद्ध होने पर भी जमानत मिल गयी और अभी फ्रैंको मुल्लकल का केस भी हमने देखा जिसमें संगीन आरोपों के बावजूद उसे रिहा किया गया । ऐसा ही एक केस जो अभी देखने को मिला वो था इंडिया टुडे के एंकर गौरव सावंत का, जिसमें उनपर पत्रकार विद्या कृष्णन ने यौन शोषण का आरोप लगाया । 🚩आपको दें कि विद्या कृष्णन जोकि the hindu में फॉर्मर हेल्थ एडिटर हैं, उन्होंने इंडिया टुडे के एग्जीक्यूटिव एडिटर गौरव सावंत पर यौन शोषण के आरोप लगाए हैं । अभी हाल ही में शुरू हुए #metoo अभियान के तहत कई ऐसे लोगों ने भी अपनी अवाज उठायी है जिनके साथ वर्षों पहले दुष्कृत्य हुआ और वे उस समय न बता पाए हों, उनमें से ही एक हैं विद्या कृष्णन । 🚩विद्या कृष्णन ने आरोप लगाया है कि अबसे 15 साल पहले 2003  जब उन्हें उनका पहला assignement मिला था मिलिट्री बेस कैम्प की रिपोर्टिंग का, तब की ये घटना है । लेकिन उस समय क्योंकि गौरव सावंत के काफी नाम था वो अपने साथ हुई घटना के बारे में लोगों को नहीं बता पाईं, लेकिन अब #metoo अभियान के तहत उन्होंने अपने साथ हुई घटना को लोगों के साथ साझा किया । 🚩अब यहाँ सवाल ये उठता है कि गौरव सावंत पर आरोप लगने के बावजूद उसपर कार्यवाही क्यों नहीं कि जा रही है ? क्या सिर्फ इसलिए कि वो एक पत्रकार हैं ? या उन्होंने अभी से ही एक मोटी रकम दे दी है ? और त
name: AzaadBharat.Org

🚩वर्तमान की स्थिति देखकर लगता है कि कानून के नियम नेता-अभिनेता एवं अमीर और पत्रकारों के लिए अलग और किसी हिंदुनिष्ठ या हिन्दू साधु-संत के लिए अलग-अलग होते हैं । किसी हिन्दू धर्म के संत या हिंदुत्व का प्रतिनिधित्व करने वालों पर मात्र एक आरोप लगने की देर होती है और उनकी गिरफ्तारी हो जाती है तथा मीडिया की झूठी कहानियों की पट्टियां भी शुरू हो जाती है , लेकिन वहीं अगर कोई नेता-अभिनेता या पत्रकार अथवा किसी अन्य धर्म के धर्म गुरु हों तो उनके द्वारा किये गए दुष्कृत्यों पर मीडिया और पुलिस मूकदर्शक बन बैठ जाते हैं और न्यायलय से उन्हें जमानत भी तुरंत दे दी जाती है । 🚩ऐसे कई केस हमने देखे तरुण तेजपाल , दीपक चौरसिया , सलमान खान , लालू यादव , विजय माल्या इन सबके आरोप सिद्ध होने पर भी जमानत मिल गयी और अभी फ्रैंको मुल्लकल का केस भी हमने देखा जिसमें संगीन आरोपों के बावजूद उसे रिहा किया गया । ऐसा ही एक केस जो अभी देखने को मिला वो था इंडिया टुडे के एंकर गौरव सावंत का , जिसमें उनपर पत्रकार विद्या कृष्णन ने यौन शोषण का आरोप लगाया । 🚩आपको दें कि विद्या कृष्णन जोकि hindu में फॉर्मर हेल्थ एडिटर हैं , उन्होंने इंडिया टुडे के एग्जीक्यूटिव एडिटर गौरव सावंत पर यौन शोषण के आरोप लगाए हैं । अभी हाल ही में शुरू हुए अभियान के तहत कई ऐसे लोगों ने भी अपनी अवाज उठायी है जिनके साथ वर्षों पहले दुष्कृत्य हुआ और वे उस समय न बता पाए हों , उनमें से ही एक हैं विद्या कृष्णन । 🚩विद्या कृष्णन ने आरोप लगाया है कि अबसे 15 साल पहले 2003 जब उन्हें उनका पहला assignement मिला था मिलिट्री बेस कैम्प की रिपोर्टिंग का , तब की ये घटना है । लेकिन उस समय क्योंकि गौरव सावंत के काफी नाम था वो अपने साथ हुई घटना के बारे में लोगों को नहीं बता पाईं , लेकिन अब अभियान के तहत उन्होंने अपने साथ हुई घटना को लोगों के साथ साझा किया । 🚩अब यहाँ सवाल ये उठता है कि गौरव सावंत पर आरोप लगने के बावजूद उसपर कार्यवाही क्यों नहीं कि जा रही है ? क्या सिर्फ इसलिए कि वो एक पत्रकार हैं ? या उन्होंने अभी से ही एक मोटी रकम दे दी है ? और त

#intothedepths ~ @breakmethod @butiyoga @themoderngoodshow @bizziegold #butiyoga #butitribe #butisattva #soulmateworkout  #igchallenge

today's challenge: who do i spend the most time in my life with, thinking about, talking to or fixating on? for each of these relationships, what needs attention first and is there a common theme to conflicts i experience with each of these people?

day 5.  today’s challenge has a twist of humor to it and i kind of hinted on this yesterday.  for example,  if i am in a relationship with someone, they do not call / text me back, answer the phone, etc? oh hayhl . . . wwwiii is about to break out!  they might have simply taken a nap or gone to the grocery store!😆 my emotional wounds are not their responsibility!  yet i have a reeeaaalllyyy difficult time not putting him in my present moment.  mhmm.  yes.✔️
.
attachment issues right der. baha!😆
another example of which all women are guilty , {including myself at the moment yet i do not want to admit yet here i go} is waiting for apologies but he / they do not know they did something wrong bc he / they should simply know! right?! ermkay then! 😆
.
ok so to answer this question.
sigh. 🙄🤦🏻‍♀️ i think about myself.  a lot.  this is with whom i spend the most time.  my mental wellness and mental health has been my top priority this year.
.
i miss my immediate family.  greatly.  i think about them.  daily.  we are not on speaking terms.  the picture is my nephew, my bubba joshy, from march 8th, the last time i saw him, kissed his face, held him close, played games with him and smelled his sweet baby skin on his forehead.♥️ this last paragraph brings me great grief 😭💔💦 i pray for healing and restoration.  soon.♥️
.
___
•
until next time ~ blessings, love, light, peace, & 
joy to each of you, my friends! ~natalie🔥🦋
•

text:
the fabulously accomplished @debrateng_actress has launched a much needed initiative in singapore called @underthecarpetsg to discuss the issues around sexual harassment and sexual assault. .

the #metoo movement that shook the rest of the world didn’t really gain any traction in singapore although @awaresingapore reported a 79% increase in cases to its sexual assault help centre in the quarter immediately after the movement went viral. clearly there is a need to address some issues that are being swept under the carpet. .

catch this powerful series on the manta pictures youtube channel! if you want to tell your story on camera or if you’d like to support this self-funded programme financially then please contact debra directly. .

text:
why do so many women not speak out about sexual harassment immediately? is a question that is often asked. to understand the answer to this question we need to look at harassment’s symbiotic relationship with guilt.
guilt and shame feed harassment by making the victim feel responsible for being subjected to the inappropriate behaviour:
“i deserve to be treated this way”, “i won’t be taken seriously if i speak out”, “i’ll get a reputation”, or worryingly “i behaved inappropriately” thus somehow inviting the behaviour.

text:
it has been a little over a month since dr. christine blasey ford's testimony. as was the case for many, that hearing rocked me to my core.

since writing about my own sexual assault almost 5 years ago, i have had the privilege of people contacting me about their own experiences. in light of the recent events, i have received a resurgence of emails and messages from people sharing their stories and seeking support. it has caused me to reflect on the distressing period after my own assault, and the words i also needed to hear at the time.

i have written a version of my response to the questions i have received, with hopes that these words will also be helpful to others. please share with the people in your life who might find comfort in this letter. ⭐️link in bio 👉

text:
👏🏼 a gift from me to you, survivor to thriver. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
in the depths of my depression, anxiety & ptsd i began learning & integrating many modes of healing, embarking on a journey that has changed my life forever. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
i have compiled the best modalities and aspects of this journey that have helped me recover and heal from sexual trauma to share with my fellow survivors. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
throughout this programme you will: ⁣⁣⁣
* reclaim your power that was once taken from you. ⁣⁣⁣
* release shame, anger and guilt. ⁣⁣⁣
* enhance and expand your self esteem & confidence. ⁣⁣⁣
* unlock your true potential. ⁣⁣⁣
* build belief and trust in your abilities. ⁣⁣⁣
* embodiment & integration of your mind, body and spirit. ⁣⁣⁣
* connection with your hearts truest desires. ⁣⁣⁣
* experience forgiveness, connection, growth and support. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
you can register for the survivor to thriver program at www.empowerthepowerful.com (link in bio) ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
love, kaity xx⁣⁣
⁣⁣

that next journey took me farther, told me not only was i not broken not only was my body ok, i was the key to the healing of the universe! yes, the torah says that moshiach (ultimate justice beauty peace completion and unity) will come when the feminine (moon!) comes out of exile and into its full, mysterious power. bring that down into some practical real life justice work? empower women’s voice, story, cycle and wisdom, give their bodies time to heal after #birth, let them speak! this, ancient jewish wisdom says, the feminine power is the key to global growth. and knowing i might be overwhelmed by this power and responsibility our sweet old torah gave me a path. she gave us a how. she told me about sacred waters and how they’ll force me to honor my cycle in immersion, she said “something so total, so womb-y wonderful, to counter how tough and painful the world is for you ladies right now”. she says “come let me tell you a secret, the western world made me a man, but i’m just as much woman as i am everything and nothing, as i am rainbow, blade of grass, temple”. she’ll say “this holy journey is for you but i’ve made sure there are safe houses on the way as you escape slavery of your sex, a mikve, a rosh chodesh circle, a ruth bader ginsberg. you have to walk this faithful path, beside shouts and screams of injustice to your fellow female, you must walk you must stay curious, you must stay vigilant, but the sacred in you is growing, all over #metoo, beside you, beneath the winter ground, seeds of change are growing, and soon they will #rise. @michelleobama

text:
ok so these are my kids! milly (policewoman) and rex (a builder who is taking a day off) i have always encouraged my kids to dress up and play any characters they want to. when it comes to tackling gender stereotypes with kids this is only half the fight. in 2017 i interviewed geena davis on gender bias in children’s programming. 
geena runs an organization to combat this, she says it wasn’t until she had a daughter and started watching little children’s entertainment that she realized there was a profound gender problem in the tv and movies that are made for, and aimed at, children. “i immediately noticed that there seemed to be far more male characters than female characters. this was stunning and made no sense: why on earth in the 21st century would we be showing fictitious worlds bereft of female characters to our children?” geena says one of the things parents can do is to chat with their children about the gender bias as and when it shows up in tv, movies or life! so this is something that i try to do! x

text:
three accessible ways to honor a child’s understanding of consent and body autonomy this holiday season (and every day):
.
👋🏾let them decide how they wish to interact with others— explore with children, before the buzz of the gatherings begins, what options are available to acknowledge people in a space. gestures such as waves, smiles, and a simple “hello” can be a great alternative to greetings involving touch. if hugs or kisses are not desired, touch options include high fives, fist bumps, and hand shakes. when children know they have choice and the power to lead how they wish to interact with others, no matter who that person is in their life, they get the chance to practice life skills that support body autonomy, safety and interpersonal communication. if a family member is unwilling to honor the boundaries and consent of the child, this is where we adults need to step up, address it and advocate for respect on their behalf.
.
📷ask before snapping, whether the child wants their picture taken— if the child is old enough to knowingly pose for a photo, they are aware of what is going on and can exercise their right to consent to being photographed or not. and if they are not verbal, pay attention to and show respect for any body language they exhibit that demonstrates a desire not to have their photo taken. it’s great practice for a lifetime ahead of digital imagery and the type of awareness we want to instill in them to protect their privacy, safety and consent. it also models for them the awareness of others’ autonomy they should exercise when they get behind the camera.
.
🍽let them decide what they wish to eat and when their body has had enough— this means steering clear of phrases like “one more bite” or “you ate broccoli last time!” or “you’re not leaving this table ‘til you finish your plate.” a child knows when they’ve had enough because their body sends them cues. we want them to grow to trust their body and have it respected by others. let them graze and communicate their wants and limits without the use of force, coercion or conflict.
.
keep #consent alive this season! ⬇️what ways are you honoring a child’s body autonomy this fall?

text:
porque tenemos que escuchar cada día: ' yo no soy feminista, pero tampoco machista', cuando el feminismo es el el principio de igualdad de derechos entre el hombre y la mujer y por tanto, quien no es feminista, es machista por definición.
porque seguimos volviendo a casa con miedo por las noches, porque sigue habiendo víctimas de la violencia de género y sigue habiendo personas que en vez de condenar tajantemente esta violencia alegan que 'también hay hombres maltratados'. porque ser mujer nos sigue poniendo en desventaja en ciertos trabajos. porque hay quien sigue preguntando 'vas a ir así vestida?' como si hubiera que enseñar a las mujeres a no provocar y no a los hombres a no tomarse un escote como un ' pasa sin llamar'. porque mis amigos me dicen cuando se mudan a ciertos barrios: 'para una chica es distinto. para mí no es peligroso, pero yo si fuera tú no viviría aquí'.
porque muchos piensan que esto es una lucha de las mujeres contra los hombres y no algo por lo que tenemos que luchar las mujeres y los hombres juntos. porque hay países en los que casan a niñas o les practican la ablación. porque  hay 'manadas' impunes. porque seguimos viviendo en un mundo en el que todas tenemos un vecino que nos tocaba el culo, o un jefe que ha intentado aprovecharse de su situación, o un desconocido que nos ha dado un susto por la calle, o un novio que se ha intentado pasar de la raya, o un borracho que no supo entender un 'no' por respuesta y decidió que si le das conversacion y luego no te quieres acostar con él eres una 'calientapollas'. porque nos 'ayudan' con las tareas domésticas como si fueran nuestras. porque algunos no entienden que no es no siempre. porque sigue sin haber igualdad de derechos entre hombtes y mujeres y por lo tanto seguimos viviendo en un mundo machista. 
sólo avanzaremos si es hacia un futuro de mujeres #libresvivasyplenas . me uno a la campaña de @animosaoficial para señalar con el dedo situaciones injustas hasta ahora normalizadas. #libresvivasyplenas #feminismo #feminist #feminism #animosaoficial #activism #niunamenos #noesno #metoo #yotecreo #women #sisterhood

text:
my friends, this evening at the qft, belfast, we screen the meeting- a remarkable movie about a remarkable woman. •
•
when ailbhe griffith was 21 years old she was violently assaulted on her way home from work. 9 years later, she sat face to face with the man who attacked her as she sought answers. this is their meeting. •
•
following tonight's screening i will be hosting a q&a with ailbhe, who plays herself in the movie, and dr marie keenan, leader in restorative justice in ireland.

text:
#monicalewinsky is telling the whole story about her white house affair with #billieeilish clinton in a three-night documentary series on a&e.

the former intern and her affair with the former president remain one of the biggest white house scandals, leading to clinton almost getting impeached.

the scandal has found a new life following the #metoo movement, with people questioning the power dynamics of the relationship.

in the first night of the documentary, lewinsky shared how the affair started. she let it all out, as seen in a transcript of the documentary from toofab, revealing that she’d had a crush on him and he’d encouraged it by being flirty.

we had a number of this flirtatious encounters, there was really no sense for me of anything beyond i have this crush and this person i have a crush on is actually paying attention to me.

she shared how at a coworker’s birthday she’d discovered her thong was showing, and rather than pull her trousers up, she thought she’d “up the game” and flash it at clinton.

i knew he was walking out of the room and instead of pulling my trousers up, i didn’t. it was unnoticeable to everybody else in the room, but he noticed.

clinton did notice and he became even more interested in her, calling her into then-communications director george stephanopoulos‘ office to talk. that was when the affair began.

i don’t think at that point in my life my heart had ever beat as fast. i blurted out, “you know i have a crush on you.” he laughed, smiled and asked me if i wanted to go into the back office and i did.

it was dark and he eventually asked me if he could kiss me and i said yes. after a little time, i went back to my desk and at some point later in the evening, i was the only person in the office and he came back in and he said if you want to meet me in the back study in 10 minutes, you can. and i did. it became more intimate from there.

she also shared clinton had all the power in the relationship, deciding if and when they saw.

text:
durante los últimos 20 años, icíar bollaín y fernando león de aranoa han sido protagonistas del cine español -entre los dos suman siete premios goya- y, al mismo tiempo, testigos privilegiados de la peripecia de una de las industrias más convulsas del sector cultural. con sus películas han iluminado algunos de los rincones más deprimidos de nuestra sociedad, dotando de dignidad a unos personajes que son el motor de su creatividad. hoy, mientras bollaín se prepara para estrenar el 14 de diciembre 'yuli', león de aranoa disfruta de un periodo de “entreguerras” en el que también está de celebración: 'barrio' cumple 20 años. con ellos hablamos de la experiencia, de etiquetas, del futuro del cine y de la resaca del #metoo.
📝javier yuste
📷 icíar bollaín y fernando león de aranoa en la cafetería del cine doré. foto: @saenphotos
➡️léelo en www.elcultural.com

#hoyenelcultural #cine #íciarbollaín #fernandoleóndearanoa #bollaín #leóndearanoa #elcultural
name: El Cultural
tweet_full:
durante los últimos 20 años, icíar bollaín y ferdo león de aranoa han sido protagonistas del cine español -entre los dos suman siete premios goya- y, al mismo tiempo, testigos privilegiados de la peripecia de una de las industrias más convulsas del sector cultural. con sus películas han iluminado algunos de los rincones más deprimidos de nuestra sociedad, dotando de dignidad a unos personajes que son el motor de su creatividad. hoy, mientras bollaín se prepara para estrenar el 14 de diciembre 'yuli', león de aranoa disfruta de un periodo de “entreguerras” en el que también está de celebración: 'barrio' cumple 20 años. con ellos hablamos de la experiencia, de etiquetas, del futuro del cine y de la resaca del #metoo.
📝javier yuste
📷 icíar bollaín y ferdo león de aranoa en la cafetería del cine doré. foto: @saenphotos
➡️léelo en www.elcultural.com

#hoyenelcultural #cine #íciarbollaín #ferdoleóndearanoa #bollaín #leóndearanoa #elcultural

text:
a world without #violence, how good does that sound? living in a #world where violence doesn’t exist would be amazing but unfortunately, within our world, there is so much violence happening daily, violence against #women and #girls.

for years women have fought for #equalrights all over the world.  whilst things are improving for some of us, the fact remains that in much of the world women do not have equal rights.  within in 2018 there is still much violence towards women and girls.  that is why from november the 25th (which is the international day for the elimination of violence against women), until december the 10th (human rights day), #unwomen are leading a #campaign entitled ‘16 days of activism against gender-based violence.’ find out more @ https://thebusinessfairy.ie/wear-orange-help-end-violence-against-women-girls/

text:
fra @daregender “i dag er det mændenes internationale dag! 
vores bestyrelsesmedlem rasmus hald møller, har gjort sig nogle tanker om, hvilke positive værdier, mænd kan bidrage med, og om den forandringsproces som maskulinitet er i gang med i disse år. vi giver ordet til rasmus: "i daregender gider vi ikke lege drengen mod pigerne – hverken i dag eller den 8. marts. vi mener, at der er masser at slås for uden at slås imod hinanden. vi mener, at maskulinitet er under forandring, ikke under pres og slet ikke ved at uddø. og vi mener at mænd og maskulinitet er betydningsfulde i arbejdet for at skabe et lige og sikkert samfund for alle – også for mændene!

mænd kan gøre en forskel i arbejdet for en lige og sikker verden for alle, når vi får øjnene op for, at idéen om ‘den rigtige mand’ er skadelig for os selv og andre mænd. “alle mænd er rigtige mænd” kan vi fortælle os selv og alle andre – ikke mindst de mænd, vi møder. for hvis der skulle være ’en rigtig mand’, så må der også være en forkert mand, og det er en ukonstruktiv måde at se mennesker på.

her er dagen så (igen) i år, og denne gang er temaet ifølge www.internationalmensday.com positive rollemodeller. jeg vil derfor gerne tegne en skitse af, hvordan jeg ser en god mandlig rollemodel anno 2018:

han har taget stilling til #metoo. han var ikke nødvendigvis med på vognen fra start, men han lyttede med og lod sig oplyse, da han kunne se, at det her problem var omfattende. som mand var han sandsynligvis en del af problemet, og som minimum kunne han i hvert fald være en del af løsningen.

han lytter efter og afviser det ikke, når hans privilegerede position pointeres. han forstår, at mange aspekter af det privilegie er usynlige for ham selv, men meget synlige for alle andre end ham, som ikke nyder godt af dette.
han viser det gerne, når han er følsom og sårbar. han tør tage røret og bestille en tid hos lægen, hvis han føler noget er galt indeni.

han tager sin barsel, også selvom kollegaer og chefer ser skævt til, når han gør det.

han har opdaget, måske på hektisk vis, at feminisme ikke er en entydig størrelse i opposition til mænd, men at man derimod kan tale om feminismer, og .. (fortsættes i kommentarspor)
name: Frejamay November

text:
[illustration by talented @maricazottinoillustration ✊🏼]
if you know me you’re well aware how i use my small social media following and art to talk about systems of abuse and start conversations. so here’s a #triggerwarning for rape & sexual assault ❗️
the last few days i read a lot about a recent rape case in ireland and, once again, my heart breaks (or maybe my anger grows? sometimes i think it’s both). this time counsel for the man aquitted of rape actually showed the underwear the victim wore during her assault and suggested to jurors, that this is proof that “she wanted it”. like putting on lace undergarments means a woman becomes public property. like the abuser was in the right because she wore something he considered sexy. like we only dress nicely so guys wanna fuck us. cause our vocal chords are only decoration and every “no” is only background noise if you compare it to a horny guys needs.
and don’t get me wrong: it’s not only guys that abuse, it’s in this case but sexual assault is not an exclusively male crime. and it’s not only shy, white girls that suffer from it- it’s all of us, especially minorities and people outside the gender binary. so please please be kind, believe people when they trust you with their stories and keep each other accountable. even in times of #metoo we are far from safe. 
i’m at work and can’t really take a picture of my underwear but i just checked and they are grey with a #wonderwoman logo on it. some might consider that sexy but it’s still not consent. shoutout to all the people taking part in this digital form of protest. you give me and many others hope. /
\
/
\
#thisisnotconsent #ibelieveher #ibelieveherireland #rape #sexualassault #political #rapeculture #rapecultureisreal #stopblamingwomen #victimblaming #corktrial

text:
#metoo can include many subtleties and nuances.  i have experienced several during my last two trips to nyc and nashville. 
in nyc city i got off the wrong subway stop and wandered around a little lost with my gps on my iphone as my companion.  this was a signal for a man to follow me for several blocks, though i made it clear i wasn’t interested. 
in nashville, party central, some guy had the audacity to grab my ponytail on the dancefloor.  later, another man approached me at the bar to tell me i was beautiful.  he also felt the need to tell me he hadn’t had sex in 12 years and in the same moment reached over and fondled other women’s breasts. 
all this under the guise of the “hunt”. men need to understand when they are on the “hunt” for women, there are two sides to this. this is a game of pursuing, persuading and conquest.  a big win for the male ego.  men in this frame of mind are ignoring the fact that they are interacting with another human being. 
a human being with a complicated history which could include sexual abuse, sexual assault, low self-esteem, depression, anxiety, and any other challenging situations.  look at the stats is likely! “be kind; everyone you meet is fighting a hard battle”

consent is very important.  no always means no.  men need to understand yes does not always mean yes.  if you have used manipulation, alcohol, or persuasion, then yes it not yes.  if you have taken advantage of your power, size or the social conditioning of women, then you’re a predator.

#metoo has given me the courage to never-ever to put up with, laugh it off, or feel obliged by this behavior.

we all have a responsibility to shine a light on this behavior and never be witness to it again.  men need to stand side-by-side with women to stop the subtleties of #metoo. 
this is not a matter of “boys being boys” this is a stand against misogyny. “bros before hoes” is not funny.  if you live by this code, you need to check yourself.  it is filled with misogyny and objectification.

i own a big debt of gratitude to all the women who came before me and created the #metoo movement.  you are all brave, beautiful souls who have opened my eyes and liberated us.
name: Sandra Elia

all this under the guise of the “hunt”. men need to understand when they are on the “hunt” for women, there are two sides to this. this is a game of pursuing, persuading and conquest.  a big win for the male ego.  men in this frame of mind are ignoring the fact that they are interacting with another human being. 
a human being with a complicated history which could include sexual abuse, sexual assault, low self-esteem, depression, anxiety, and any other challenging situations.  look at the stats is likely! “be kind; everyone you meet is fighting a hard battle”

consent is very important.  no always means no.  men need to understand yes does not always mean yes.  if you have used manipulation, alcohol, or persuasion, then yes it not yes.  if you have taken advantage of your power, size or the social conditioning of women, then you’re a predator.

#metoo has given me the courage to never-ever to put up with, laugh it off, or feel obliged by this behavior.

we all have a responsibility to shine a light on this behavior and never be witness to it again.  men need to stand side-by-side with women to stop the subtleties of #metoo.

i own a big debt of gratitude to all the women who came before me and created the #metoo movement.  you are all brave, beautiful souls who have opened my eyes and liberated us.

text:
if you grew up in the 1990s, you’ll likely be familiar with inem, the sexy housemaid in a racy soap opera titled "inem pelayan seksi" ("inem the sexy housemaid").
•
adapted from the box office film "inem pelayan sexy" in 1976, the soap opera was a runaway success.
•
in the soap opera, inem was played by rika callebaute, the daughter of doris callebaute, who played the original inem in the 1976 movie.
•
the story will soon be revived in the upcoming film adaptation "inem pelayan seksi new," helmed by hasto broto.
•
hasto said the new inem will be "acceptable to millennials."
•
the young, beautiful and sexy housemaid this time will be played by jelita callebaute, rika's younger sister.
•
in this movie, inem is a "janda muda" ("young widow") who has to put up with a lot of sexual innuendos and harassment from men.
•
the original inem, doris callebaute, will make a cameo in the movie.
•
inem pelayan seksi new will begin filming on nov. 16.
•
do you think the character of a "sexy housemaid" is still defensible in this #metoo age? have your say in the comments below.
•
photo courtesy of jelita callebaute's official instagram •
#inempelayanseksi

text:
hello, everyone.  my name is richard santiago and i’m contacting you to share a film i’m working on about my good friend, a register nurse, jason b. almeida. jason was a young man who committed suicide after years of workplace bullying.  this film documents his life and heartbreaking death.  we are doing a world-wide premier of this teaser trailer on nov. 21st 2018, to help launch the gofundme page we’ve created to complete this film.  we are also launching a page on our website,  http://www.thebullyexposed.com/jasons-story/, to offer perks for those who donate to help us complete this project.  please share this post and link to all your friends and family.  help us tell jason’s story.

don’t just share this post one time. please share it every wednesday to honor jason’s life. keep sharing until the project is funded.

check out these videos to learn more about our project to honor jason:

dear bully pitch video
https://vimeo.com/300931778  dear bully teaser:  the jason bennett almeida story
 https://vimeo.com/300930280

the bully exposed gofundme page
https://www.gofundme.com/telljasonstory 
film perk page
http://www.thebullyexposed.com/jasons-story/

thebullyexposed.com is a 501 (c) 3 non-profit group and all donations are tax deductible. 
#telljasonstory #tbe #thebullyexposed #metoo #makeitstop #standuptobullies #instabully #instagram #instapic #blacklivesmatter #bully #bullying #stopbullying #makeithappen #makeitorbreakit #workplacebullying #workplace

text:
trans-feminine folks face the highest rate of sexual harassment and abuse among the lgbti population. ll, a friend of the community, admitted that her own father raped her multiple times when she was in her teens, claiming that he wanted to help her "be a woman." she, like so many other sexual abuse survivors never reported him to the police for fear of having to recount her traumatic experiences, or being told that she only had herself to blame. trans-women are women, just like trans-men are men. a person's desires should not be allowed to infringe another's human rights, just as much as their religious or political beliefs don't either.
---
kaum transpuan merupakan golongan yang mengalami pelecehan dan kekerasan seksual tertinggi dibandingan dengan golongan lgbti lainnya. ll, seorang teman komunitas kami mengaku pernah diperkosa berkulang kali oleh ayahnya sendiri, dengan dalih membantunya untuk "menjadi seorang perempuan." seperti laiknya penyintas kekerasan seksual lainnya, ll tidak melaporkan ke polisi karena tidak ingin dipaksa mengingat kembali pengalaman traumatisnya, dan karena takut dirinya sendiri yang dianggap menyebabkan perbuatan hina itu. trans-puan adalah perempuan, sama seperti trans-pria adalah pria. nafsu seseorang tidak boleh melampaui hak asasi manusia lainnya, sama seperti pandangan agama dan politiknya tidak membuat mereka berhak melecehkan orang lain.
---

text:
#metoo is not about gender, it's about power
.
sexual assault and rape are about power, and this despicable behavior impacts all of us including men
.
we need to believe all victims. respect them. we need to give them space to tell their stories.
.
this international men's day, let's take this a step further and stop gendering the movement.
.
.
